-- European Union CO2 Permits to Rise to 22 Euros in 2011, Point Carbon Says
-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 2010-12-08T12:09:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-08/european-union-co2-permits-to-rise-to-22-euros-in-2011-point-carbon-says.html
European Union carbon emission
permits may rise to 22 euros a metric ton next year, Point
Carbon said in an e-mailed statement today.  Point Carbon, the Oslo-based provider of research on
emission markets, forecast carbon permits to increase to 25
euros in 2012 and 36 euros in 2020.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Catherine Airlie at 
